What I think about bittensor: It is the best AI related Blockchain project on the market.. A lot of innovation goes on.  
https://bittensor.com/whitepaper

https://bittensor.com/documentation/subnetworks/subnetworks

However I found four issues:

1. Validators can't assess miners correctly if the miners are smarter than themselves.. you can get bad ratings if you are smarter than your peers. To use an anology: if the teacher doesn't know anything about a topic he can only rate the form.. the result could be something which sounds good but is  totally fictional.. and this can be witnessed already...

2. Low synergy: your model doesn't improve automatically from the validation process.. but miners can improve the software and it seems like some already did. But the knowledge isn't shared because of the competition.

3. conflict of interest if miners and validators are controlled by the same entity. There are some game-theory measurements in place in order to prevent this.. but in my opinion it already takes place.

4. Decentralized mixture of experts (dMoE) is a feature that will increase the 'smart miner' problem, because experts (specialized miner) are receiving ratings from generalists (validators)..
Additionally, dMoE  has the potential to kill the project in total, if it is implemented the wrong way. The main risk here is that early validators become gate keepers. This will lead to centralization of power and slow down progress, censorship..

My advice: The project is very important and freedom and privacy fighters should get involved if possible.
